{
  "stem": "20405.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[CRYING] We had our own house in the neighborhood, yes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The what?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To us, it was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we're born over there with two rooms, kitchen, living room, and a big lot in front of the house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Which later, we sold our house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father built up a two story house in that lot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there is there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were living very beautiful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [INAUDIBLE] were happy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My Jewish life?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, actually my grandfather, I remember, he was at that time around 60, 65 years old.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He never was so religious at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was living with them, my father, my grandfather, and my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he used to wake me up every morning around 6:00 to take me to the temple.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Which, that was until I became 13.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And, I got me-- and I got a bar mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "After that, I say, maybe six months, something like that, they sent me in Italy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because my father died at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was the older.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My mother was with four kids.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the Italian consulate, because we were Italian citizens, even if you born, everybody born in Greece, we were Italian citizen.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they send me in Italy, in Milan, to a college.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- their name, my grandfather name, was like my name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I took after him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was more Morris.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandmother, she-- they used to call her Dudune, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because she was beautiful [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Turkish, Dudune means something good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know what it means, but something very nice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because they loved me so much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father passed away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had his name, my grandfather name.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
